This change is compatible with JDK6-8, because you only add an entry to `MANIFEST.mf` file. Older Java versions simply ignore it, and JDK9 uses it as a stable automatic module name (instead of generating it from JAR archive name).

If you drop the support for older JDKs somewhere in the future, you can create a true module with the same name and the change will be invisible to JDK9 modular applications:

```java
module org.mockito {
   requires ...;
}
```

